    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-07-13T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-07-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="373"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d373">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Dupuy de Lôme</persName> to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of Spain</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Boston</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-07-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 13, 1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: I have received here the note of
                    Mr. Adee in regard to the Mora claim.</p>
                <p>Before leaving Washington I told Mr. Adee that I had been advised that in a very
                    few days that long-pending question would be settled.</p>
                <p>The Duke of Tetuan has kept me informed by cable of every step of the action
                    taken in regard to that matter. I am sure that a very few days, no more than are
                    necessary to comply with our internal procedure, will bring the final solution
                    of the question.</p>
                <p>So soon as I shall be informed of the proceedings of the cabinet meetings, I
                    shall have the honor to communicate them to you.</p>
                <p>Believe me, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">E. Dupuy de Lôme</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
